  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Report from Jerusalem'
      title: Report from Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Nehemiah the son of Hacaliah.Now it happened in the
        month of Chislev, in the twentieth year, as I was in Susa the citadel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that Hanani, one of my brothers, came with certain men from Judah.
        And I asked them concerning the Jews who escaped, who had survived the exile,
        and concerning Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: "3: Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 3
      content: "And they said to me, \u201CThe remnant there in the province who
        had survived the exile is in great trouble and shame. The wall of Jerusalem
        is broken down, and its gates are destroyed by fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As soon as I heard these words I sat down and wept and mourned for
        days, and I continued fasting and praying before the God of heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of heaven, the
        great and awesome God who keeps covenant and steadfast love with those who
        love him and keep his commandments, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "let your ear be attentive and your eyes open, to hear the prayer
        of your servant that I now pray before you day and night for the people of
        Israel your servants, confessing the sins of the people of Israel, which
        we have sinned against you. Even I and my father\u2019s house have sinned. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'We have acted very corruptly against you and have not kept the commandments,
        the statutes, and the rules that you commanded your servant Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Remember the word that you commanded your servant Moses, saying,
        \u2018If you are unfaithful, I will scatter you among the peoples, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but if you return to me and keep my commandments and do them, though
        your outcasts are in the uttermost parts of heaven, from there I will gather
        them and bring them to the place that I have chosen, to make my name dwell
        there.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They are your servants and your people, whom you have redeemed by
        your great power and by your strong hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "O Lord, let your ear be attentive to the prayer of your servant,
        and to the prayer of your servants who delight to fear your name, and give
        success to your servant today, and grant him mercy in the sight of this man.\u201DNow
        I was cupbearer to the king."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Sent to Judah'
      title: Nehemiah Sent to Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  In the month of Nisan, in the twentieth year of King Artaxerxes,
        when wine was before him, I took up the wine and gave it to the king. Now
        I had not been sad in his presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king said to me, \u201CWhy is your face sad, seeing you are
        not sick? This is nothing but sadness of the heart.\u201D Then I was very
        much afraid. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I said to the king, \u201CLet the king live forever! Why should not
        my face be sad, when the city, the place of my fathers\u2019 graves, lies
        in ruins, and its gates have been destroyed by fire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king said to me, \u201CWhat are you requesting?\u201D So
        I prayed to the God of heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, and if your
        servant has found favor in your sight, that you send me to Judah, to the
        city of my fathers\u2019 graves, that I may rebuild it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the king said to me (the queen sitting beside him), \u201CHow
        long will you be gone, and when will you return?\u201D So it pleased the
        king to send me when I had given him a time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And I said to the king, \u201CIf it pleases the king, let letters
        be given me to the governors of the province Beyond the River, that they
        may let me pass through until I come to Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: "8: Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem\u2019s Walls"
      title: "Nehemiah Inspects Jerusalem\u2019s Walls"
      number: 8
      content: "and a letter to Asaph, the keeper of the king\u2019s forest, that
        he may give me timber to make beams for the gates of the fortress of the
        temple, and for the wall of the city, and for the house that I shall occupy.\u201D
        And the king granted me what I asked, for the good hand of my God was upon
        me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then I came to the governors of the province Beyond the River and
        gave them the king\u2019s letters. Now the king had sent with me officers
        of the army and horsemen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But when Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite servant heard
        this, it displeased them greatly that someone had come to seek the welfare
        of the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  So I went to Jerusalem and was there three days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then I arose in the night, I and a few men with me. And I told no
        one what my God had put into my heart to do for Jerusalem. There was no animal
        with me but the one on which I rode. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I went out by night by the Valley Gate to the Dragon Spring and to
        the Dung Gate, and I inspected the walls of Jerusalem that were broken down
        and its gates that had been destroyed by fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then I went on to the Fountain Gate and to the King\u2019s Pool,
        but there was no room for the animal that was under me to pass. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then I went up in the night by the valley and inspected the wall,
        and I turned back and entered by the Valley Gate, and so returned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the officials did not know where I had gone or what I was doing,
        and I had not yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials,
        and the rest who were to do the work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I said to them, \u201CYou see the trouble we are in, how Jerusalem
        lies in ruins with its gates burned. Come, let us build the wall of Jerusalem,
        that we may no longer suffer derision.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I told them of the hand of my God that had been upon me for good,
        and also of the words that the king had spoken to me. And they said, \u201CLet
        us rise up and build.\u201D So they strengthened their hands for the good
        work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But when Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite servant and
        Geshem the Arab heard of it, they jeered at us and despised us and said,
        \u201CWhat is this thing that you are doing? Are you rebelling against the
        king?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then I replied to them, \u201CThe God of heaven will make us prosper,
        and we his servants will arise and build, but you have no portion or right
        or claim[[COMMENT(0)]] in Jerusalem.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '2:20 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rebuilding the Wall'
      title: Rebuilding the Wall
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brothers the priests,
        and they built the Sheep Gate. They consecrated it and set its doors. They
        consecrated it as far as the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Tower of
        Hananel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And next to him the men of Jericho built. And next to them[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Zaccur the son of Imri built.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The sons of Hassenaah built the Fish Gate. They laid its beams and
        set its doors, its bolts, and its bars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And next to them Meremoth the son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz repaired.
        And next to them Meshullam the son of Berechiah, son of Meshezabel repaired.
        And next to them Zadok the son of Baana repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And next to them the Tekoites repaired, but their nobles would not
        stoop to serve their Lord.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Joiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah repaired
        the Gate of Yeshanah.[[COMMENT(0)]]  They laid its beams and set its doors,
        its bolts, and its bars. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And next to them repaired Melatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite,
        the men of Gibeon and of Mizpah, the seat of the governor of the province
        Beyond the River. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Next to them Uzziel the son of Harhaiah, goldsmiths, repaired. Next
        to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, repaired, and they restored Jerusalem
        as far as the Broad Wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, ruler of half the district
        of[[COMMENT(0)]] Jerusalem, repaired. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        content: Or ; also verses 12, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph repaired opposite his house.
        And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabneiah repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Malchijah the son of Harim and Hasshub the son of Pahath-moab repaired
        another section and the Tower of the Ovens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Next to him Shallum the son of Hallohesh, ruler of half the district
        of Jerusalem, repaired, he and his daughters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired the Valley Gate. They
        rebuilt it and set its doors, its bolts, and its bars, and repaired a thousand
        cubits[[COMMENT(0)]] of the wall, as far as the Dung Gate.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Malchijah the son of Rechab, ruler of the district of Beth-haccherem,
        repaired the Dung Gate. He rebuilt it and set its doors, its bolts, and its
        bars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Shallum the son of Col-hozeh, ruler of the district of Mizpah,
        repaired the Fountain Gate. He rebuilt it and covered it and set its doors,
        its bolts, and its bars. And he built the wall of the Pool of Shelah of the
        king\u2019s garden, as far as the stairs that go down from the city of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, ruler of half the district of
        Beth-zur, repaired to a point opposite the tombs of David, as far as the
        artificial pool, and as far as the house of the mighty men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After him the Levites repaired: Rehum the son of Bani. Next to him
        Hashabiah, ruler of half the district of Keilah, repaired for his district. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After him their brothers repaired: Bavvai the son of Henadad, ruler
        of half the district of Keilah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, ruler of Mizpah, repaired another
        section opposite the ascent to the armory at the buttress.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:19 '
        content: Or ; also verses 20, 24, 25
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After him Baruch the son of Zabbai repaired[[COMMENT(0)]] another
        section from the buttress to the door of the house of Eliashib the high priest. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:20 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'After him Meremoth the son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz repaired another
        section from the door of the house of Eliashib to the end of the house of
        Eliashib. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'After him the priests, the men of the surrounding area, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'After them Benjamin and Hasshub repaired opposite their house. After
        them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, son of Ananiah repaired beside his own
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section, from
        the house of Azariah to the buttress and to the corner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Palal the son of Uzai repaired opposite the buttress and the tower
        projecting from the upper house of the king at the court of the guard. After
        him Pedaiah the son of Parosh '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and the temple servants living on Ophel repaired to a point opposite
        the Water Gate on the east and the projecting tower. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'After him the Tekoites repaired another section opposite the great
        projecting tower as far as the wall of Ophel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Above the Horse Gate the priests repaired, each one opposite his
        own house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'After them Zadok the son of Immer repaired opposite his own house.
        After him Shemaiah the son of Shecaniah, the keeper of the East Gate, repaired. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah and Hanun the sixth son of
        Zalaph repaired another section. After him Meshullam the son of Berechiah
        repaired opposite his chamber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'After him Malchijah, one of the goldsmiths, repaired as far as the
        house of the temple servants and of the merchants, opposite the Muster Gate,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and to the upper chamber of the corner. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:31 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: And between the upper chamber of the corner and the Sheep Gate the
        goldsmiths and the merchants repaired.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Opposition to the Work'
      title: Opposition to the Work
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] Now when Sanballat heard that we were building
        the wall, he was angry and greatly enraged, and he jeered at the Jews. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: '  Ch 3:33 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he said in the presence of his brothers and of the army of Samaria,
        \u201CWhat are these feeble Jews doing? Will they restore it for themselves?[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Will they sacrifice? Will they finish up in a day? Will they revive the stones
        out of the heaps of rubbish, and burned ones at that?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:2 '
        content: 'Or   '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him, and he said, \u201CYes, what
        they are building\u2014if a fox goes up on it he will break down their stone
        wall!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hear, O our God, for we are despised. Turn back their taunt on their
        own heads and give them up to be plundered in a land where they are captives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not cover their guilt, and let not their sin be blotted out from
        your sight, for they have provoked you to anger in the presence of the builders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So we built the wall. And all the wall was joined together to half
        its height, for the people had a mind to work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]] But when Sanballat and Tobiah and the Arabs and
        the Ammonites and the Ashdodites heard that the repairing of the walls of
        Jerusalem was going forward and that the breaches were beginning to be closed,
        they were very angry. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: '  Ch 4:1 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they all plotted together to come and fight against Jerusalem
        and to cause confusion in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And we prayed to our God and set a guard as a protection against
        them day and night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "In Judah it was said,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CThe strength of those who
        bear the burdens is failing. There is too much rubble. By ourselves we will
        not be able to rebuild the wall.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And our enemies said, \u201CThey will not know or see till we come
        among them and kill them and stop the work.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "At that time the Jews who lived near them came from all directions
        and said to us ten times, \u201CYou must return to us.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:12 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So in the lowest parts of the space behind the wall, in open places,
        I stationed the people by their clans, with their swords, their spears, and
        their bows. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Work Resumes'
      title: The Work Resumes
      number: 14
      content: "And I looked and arose and said to the nobles and to the officials
        and to the rest of the people, \u201CDo not be afraid of them. Remember the
        Lord, who is great and awesome, and fight for your brothers, your sons, your
        daughters, your wives, and your homes.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When our enemies heard that it was known to us and that God had frustrated
        their plan, we all returned to the wall, each to his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'From that day on, half of my servants worked on construction, and
        half held the spears, shields, bows, and coats of mail. And the leaders stood
        behind the whole house of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'who were building on the wall. Those who carried burdens were loaded
        in such a way that each labored on the work with one hand and held his weapon
        with the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And each of the builders had his sword strapped at his side while
        he built. The man who sounded the trumpet was beside me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And I said to the nobles and to the officials and to the rest of
        the people, \u201CThe work is great and widely spread, and we are separated
        on the wall, far from one another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "In the place where you hear the sound of the trumpet, rally to us
        there. Our God will fight for us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So we labored at the work, and half of them held the spears from
        the break of dawn until the stars came out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I also said to the people at that time, \u201CLet every man and his
        servant pass the night within Jerusalem, that they may be a guard for us
        by night and may labor by day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So neither I nor my brothers nor my servants nor the men of the guard
        who followed me, none of us took off our clothes; each kept his weapon at
        his right hand.[[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: '4:23 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nehemiah Stops Oppression of the Poor'
      title: Nehemiah Stops Oppression of the Poor
      number: 1
      content: '  Now there arose a great outcry of the people and of their wives
        against their Jewish brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For there were those who said, \u201CWith our sons and our daughters,
        we are many. So let us get grain, that we may eat and keep alive.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "There were also those who said, \u201CWe are mortgaging our fields,
        our vineyards, and our houses to get grain because of the famine.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And there were those who said, \u201CWe have borrowed money for the
        king\u2019s tax on our fields and our vineyards. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now our flesh is as the flesh of our brothers, our children are as
        their children. Yet we are forcing our sons and our daughters to be slaves,
        and some of our daughters have already been enslaved, but it is not in our
        power to help it, for other men have our fields and our vineyards.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I was very angry when I heard their outcry and these words. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "I took counsel with myself, and I brought charges against the nobles
        and the officials. I said to them, \u201CYou are exacting interest, each
        from his brother.\u201D And I held a great assembly against them "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and said to them, \u201CWe, as far as we are able, have bought back
        our Jewish brothers who have been sold to the nations, but you even sell
        your brothers that they may be sold to us!\u201D They were silent and could
        not find a word to say. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So I said, \u201CThe thing that you are doing is not good. Ought
        you not to walk in the fear of our God to prevent the taunts of the nations
        our enemies? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Moreover, I and my brothers and my servants are lending them money
        and grain. Let us abandon this exacting of interest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Return to them this very day their fields, their vineyards, their
        olive orchards, and their houses, and the percentage of money, grain, wine,
        and oil that you have been exacting from them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they said, \u201CWe will restore these and require nothing from
        them. We will do as you say.\u201D And I called the priests and made them
        swear to do as they had promised. "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Nehemiah\u2019s Generosity"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Generosity"
      number: 13
      content: "I also shook out the fold[[COMMENT(0)]] of my garment and said, \u201CSo
        may God shake out every man from his house and from his labor who does not
        keep this promise. So may he be shaken out and emptied.\u201D And all the
        assembly said \u201CAmen\u201D and praised the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And the people did as they had promised.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover, from the time that I was appointed to be their governor
        in the land of Judah, from the twentieth year to the thirty-second year of
        Artaxerxes the king, twelve years, neither I nor my brothers ate the food
        allowance of the governor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The former governors who were before me laid heavy burdens on the
        people and took from them for their daily ration[[COMMENT(0)]] forty shekels
        of silver. Even their servants lorded it over the people. But I did not do
        so, because of the fear of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:15 '
        content: Compare Vulgate; Hebrew A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I also persevered in the work on this wall, and we acquired no land,
        and all my servants were gathered there for the work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover, there were at my table 150 men, Jews and officials, besides
        those who came to us from the nations that were around us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now what was prepared at my expense[[COMMENT(0)]] for each day was
        one ox and six choice sheep and birds, and every ten days all kinds of wine
        in abundance. Yet for all this I did not demand the food allowance of the
        governor, because the service was too heavy on this people. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Remember for my good, O my God, all that I have done for this people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conspiracy Against Nehemiah'
      title: Conspiracy Against Nehemiah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when Sanballat and Tobiah and Geshem the Arab and the rest
        of our enemies heard that I had built the wall and that there was no breach
        left in it (although up to that time I had not set up the doors in the gates), '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Sanballat and Geshem sent to me, saying, \u201CCome and let us meet
        together at Hakkephirim in the plain of Ono.\u201D But they intended to do
        me harm. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I sent messengers to them, saying, \u201CI am doing a great work
        and I cannot come down. Why should the work stop while I leave it and come
        down to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they sent to me four times in this way, and I answered them in
        the same manner. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In the same way Sanballat for the fifth time sent his servant to
        me with an open letter in his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "In it was written, \u201CIt is reported among the nations, and Geshem[[COMMENT(0)]]
        also says it, that you and the Jews intend to rebel; that is why you are
        building the wall. And according to these reports you wish to become their
        king. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you have also set up prophets to proclaim concerning you in Jerusalem,
        \u2018There is a king in Judah.\u2019 And now the king will hear of these
        reports. So now come and let us take counsel together.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then I sent to him, saying, \u201CNo such things as you say have
        been done, for you are inventing them out of your own mind.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For they all wanted to frighten us, thinking, \u201CTheir hands will
        drop from the work, and it will not be done.\u201D But now, O God,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        strengthen my hands.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now when I went into the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, son
        of Mehetabel, who was confined to his home, he said, \u201CLet us meet together
        in the house of God, within the temple. Let us close the doors of the temple,
        for they are coming to kill you. They are coming to kill you by night.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But I said, \u201CShould such a man as I run away? And what man such
        as I could go into the temple and live?[[COMMENT(0)]] I will not go in.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I understood and saw that God had not sent him, but he had pronounced
        the prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For this purpose he was hired, that I should be afraid and act in
        this way and sin, and so they could give me a bad name in order to taunt
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Wall Is Finished'
      title: The Wall Is Finished
      number: 14
      content: 'Remember Tobiah and Sanballat, O my God, according to these things
        that they did, and also the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the prophets
        who wanted to make me afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth day of the month Elul,
        in fifty-two days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And when all our enemies heard of it, all the nations around us were
        afraid and fell greatly in their own esteem, for they perceived that this
        work had been accomplished with the help of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Moreover, in those days the nobles of Judah sent many letters to
        Tobiah, and Tobiah\u2019s letters came to them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For many in Judah were bound by oath to him, because he was the son-in-law
        of Shecaniah the son of Arah: and his son Jehohanan had taken the daughter
        of Meshullam the son of Berechiah as his wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Also they spoke of his good deeds in my presence and reported my words
        to him. And Tobiah sent letters to make me afraid.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Now when the wall had been built and I had set up the doors, and
        the gatekeepers, the singers, and the Levites had been appointed, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I gave my brother Hanani and Hananiah the governor of the castle
        charge over Jerusalem, for he was a more faithful and God-fearing man than
        many. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to them, \u201CLet not the gates of Jerusalem be opened
        until the sun is hot. And while they are still standing guard, let them shut
        and bar the doors. Appoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem,
        some at their guard posts and some in front of their own homes.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Lists of Returned Exiles'
      title: Lists of Returned Exiles
      number: 4
      content: 'The city was wide and large, but the people within it were few, and
        no houses had been rebuilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then my God put it into my heart to assemble the nobles and the officials
        and the people to be enrolled by genealogy. And I found the book of the genealogy
        of those who came up at the first, and I found written in it:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  These were the people of the province who came up out of the captivity
        of those exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried into
        exile. They returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his town. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani,
        Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah.The number of the men
        of the people of Israel: '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'the sons of Parosh, 2,172. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The sons of Shephatiah, 372. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The sons of Arah, 652. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The sons of Pahath-moab, namely the sons of Jeshua and Joab, 2,818. '
      comments: []
