      content: 'The sons of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, 721. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'The sons of Senaah, 3,930.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'The priests: the sons of Jedaiah, namely the house of Jeshua, 973. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The sons of Immer, 1,052. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'The sons of Pashhur, 1,247. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'The sons of Harim, 1,017.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, namely of Kadmiel of the sons of
        Hodevah, 74. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'The singers: the sons of Asaph, 148. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons
        of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, the sons of Shobai, 138.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'The temple servants: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons
        of Tabbaoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'the sons of Keros, the sons of Sia, the sons of Padon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'the sons of Lebana, the sons of Hagaba, the sons of Shalmai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'the sons of Hanan, the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'the sons of Reaiah, the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'the sons of Gazzam, the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'the sons of Besai, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephushesim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'the sons of Bazlith, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha, '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Temah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'the sons of Neziah, the sons of Hatipha.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: "The sons of Solomon\u2019s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons
        of Sophereth, the sons of Perida, "
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim,
        the sons of Amon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: "All the temple servants and the sons of Solomon\u2019s servants were
        392.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: "  The following were those who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha,
        Cherub, Addon, and Immer, but they could not prove their fathers\u2019 houses
        nor their descent, whether they belonged to Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 642. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Also, of the priests: the sons of Hobaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the
        sons of Barzillai (who had taken a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the
        Gileadite and was called by their name). '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'These sought their registration among those enrolled in the genealogies,
        but it was not found there, so they were excluded from the priesthood as
        unclean. '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: Totals of People and Gifts'
      title: Totals of People and Gifts
      number: 65
      content: 'The governor told them that they were not to partake of the most
        holy food until a priest with Urim and Thummim should arise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: 'The whole assembly together was 42,360, '
      comments: []
    - name: '67: '
      title: 
      number: 67
      content: 'besides their male and female servants, of whom there were 7,337.
        And they had 245 singers, male and female. '
      comments: []
    - name: '68: '
      title: 
      number: 68
      content: 'Their horses were 736, their mules 245,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:68 '
        content: 'Compare Ezra 2:66 and the margins of some Hebrew manuscripts; Hebrew
          lacks '
    - name: '69: '
      title: 
      number: 69
      content: 'their camels 435, and their donkeys 6,720.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '70: '
      title: 
      number: 70
      content: "Now some of the heads of fathers\u2019 houses gave to the work. The
        governor gave to the treasury 1,000 darics[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, 50 basins,
        30 priests\u2019 garments and 500 minas of silver.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:70 '
        content: 'A was a coin weighing about 1/4 ounce or 8.5 gramsA was about 1
          1/4 pounds or 0.6 kilogramProbable reading; Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '71: '
      title: 
      number: 71
      content: "And some of the heads of fathers\u2019 houses gave into the treasury
        of the work 20,000 darics of gold and 2,200 minas of silver. "
      comments: []
    - name: '72: '
      title: 
      number: 72
      content: "And what the rest of the people gave was 20,000 darics of gold, 2,000
        minas of silver, and 67 priests\u2019 garments.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '73: '
      title: 
      number: 73
      content: So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of
        the people, the temple servants, and all Israel, lived in their towns.  And
        when the seventh month had come, the people of Israel were in their towns.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ezra Reads the Law'
      title: Ezra Reads the Law
      number: 1
      content: '  And all the people gathered as one man into the square before the
        Water Gate. And they told Ezra the scribe to bring the Book of the Law of
        Moses that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Ezra the priest brought the Law before the assembly, both men
        and women and all who could understand what they heard, on the first day
        of the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he read from it facing the square before the Water Gate from
        early morning until midday, in the presence of the men and the women and
        those who could understand. And the ears of all the people were attentive
        to the Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And Ezra the scribe stood on a wooden platform that they had made
        for the purpose. And beside him stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah,
        and Maaseiah on his right hand, and Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum,
        Hashbaddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam on his left hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was
        above all the people, and as he opened it all the people stood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Ezra blessed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the great God,
        and all the people answered, \u201CAmen, Amen,\u201D lifting up their hands.
        And they bowed their heads and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        with their faces to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah,
        Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, the Levites,[[COMMENT(0)]]  helped
        the people to understand the Law, while the people remained in their places. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: 'Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: This Day Is Holy'
      title: This Day Is Holy
      number: 8
      content: 'They read from the book, from the Law of God, clearly,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and they gave the sense, so that the people understood the reading.  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:8 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Nehemiah, who was the governor, and Ezra the priest and scribe,
        and the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, \u201CThis
        day is holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God; do not mourn or
        weep.\u201D For all the people wept as they heard the words of the Law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CGo your way. Eat the fat and drink sweet
        wine and send portions to anyone who has nothing ready, for this day is holy
        to our Lord. And do not be grieved, for the joy of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is your strength.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So the Levites calmed all the people, saying, \u201CBe quiet, for
        this day is holy; do not be grieved.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Feast of Booths Celebrated'
      title: Feast of Booths Celebrated
      number: 12
      content: 'And all the people went their way to eat and drink and to send portions
        and to make great rejoicing, because they had understood the words that were
        declared to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "On the second day the heads of fathers\u2019 houses of all the people,
        with the priests and the Levites, came together to Ezra the scribe in order
        to study the words of the Law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And they found it written in the Law that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded by Moses that the people of Israel should dwell in booths[[COMMENT(0)]]
        during the feast of the seventh month, '
      comments:
      - number: '8:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and that they should proclaim it and publish it in all their towns
        and in Jerusalem, \u201CGo out to the hills and bring branches of olive,
        wild olive, myrtle, palm, and other leafy trees to make booths, as it is
        written.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So the people went out and brought them and made booths for themselves,
        each on his roof, and in their courts and in the courts of the house of God,
        and in the square at the Water Gate and in the square at the Gate of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And all the assembly of those who had returned from the captivity
        made booths and lived in the booths, for from the days of Jeshua the son
        of Nun to that day the people of Israel had not done so. And there was very
        great rejoicing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And day by day, from the first day to the last day, he read from the
        Book of the Law of God. They kept the feast seven days, and on the eighth
        day there was a solemn assembly, according to the rule.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People of Israel Confess Their Sin'
      title: The People of Israel Confess Their Sin
      number: 1
      content: '  Now on the twenty-fourth day of this month the people of Israel
        were assembled with fasting and in sackcloth, and with earth on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the Israelites[[COMMENT(0)]] separated themselves from all foreigners
        and stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their fathers. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew   '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they stood up in their place and read from the Book of the Law
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God for a quarter of the day; for
        another quarter of it they made confession and worshiped the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'On the stairs of the Levites stood Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah,
        Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani; and they cried with a loud voice to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> their God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah,
        Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah, said, \u201CStand up and bless the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God from everlasting to everlasting. Blessed be your glorious name,
        which is exalted above all blessing and praise.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CYou are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        you alone. You have made heaven, the heaven of heavens, with all their host,
        the earth and all that is on it, the seas and all that is in them; and you
        preserve all of them; and the host of heaven worships you. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: '  Septuagint adds     '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God who chose Abram
        and brought him out of Ur of the Chaldeans and gave him the name Abraham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You found his heart faithful before you, and made with him the covenant
        to give to his offspring the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite,
        the Perizzite, the Jebusite, and the Girgashite. And you have kept your promise,
        for you are righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  \u201CAnd you saw the affliction of our fathers in Egypt and heard
        their cry at the Red Sea, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and performed signs and wonders against Pharaoh and all his servants
        and all the people of his land, for you knew that they acted arrogantly against
        our fathers. And you made a name for yourself, as it is to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you divided the sea before them, so that they went through the
        midst of the sea on dry land, and you cast their pursuers into the depths,
        as a stone into mighty waters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'By a pillar of cloud you led them in the day, and by a pillar of
        fire in the night to light for them the way in which they should go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You came down on Mount Sinai and spoke with them from heaven and
        gave them right rules and true laws, good statutes and commandments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and you made known to them your holy Sabbath and commanded them commandments
        and statutes and a law by Moses your servant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You gave them bread from heaven for their hunger and brought water
        for them out of the rock for their thirst, and you told them to go in to
        possess the land that you had sworn to give them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CBut they and our fathers acted presumptuously and stiffened
        their neck and did not obey your commandments. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'They refused to obey and were not mindful of the wonders that you
        performed among them, but they stiffened their neck and appointed a leader
        to return to their slavery in Egypt.[[COMMENT(0)]] But you are a God ready
        to forgive, gracious and merciful, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast
        love, and did not forsake them. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:17 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts; many Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Even when they had made for themselves a golden[[COMMENT(0)]] calf
        and said, \u2018This is your God who brought you up out of Egypt,\u2019 and
        had committed great blasphemies, "
      comments:
      - number: '9:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew   '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'you in your great mercies did not forsake them in the wilderness.
        The pillar of cloud to lead them in the way did not depart from them by day,
        nor the pillar of fire by night to light for them the way by which they should
        go. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You gave your good Spirit to instruct them and did not withhold your
        manna from their mouth and gave them water for their thirst. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Forty years you sustained them in the wilderness, and they lacked
        nothing. Their clothes did not wear out and their feet did not swell.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CAnd you gave them kingdoms and peoples and allotted to them
        every corner. So they took possession of the land of Sihon king of Heshbon
        and the land of Og king of Bashan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You multiplied their children as the stars of heaven, and you brought
        them into the land that you had told their fathers to enter and possess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So the descendants went in and possessed the land, and you subdued
        before them the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, and gave them into
        their hand, with their kings and the peoples of the land, that they might
        do with them as they would. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And they captured fortified cities and a rich land, and took possession
        of houses full of all good things, cisterns already hewn, vineyards, olive
        orchards and fruit trees in abundance. So they ate and were filled and became
        fat and delighted themselves in your great goodness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  \u201CNevertheless, they were disobedient and rebelled against
        you and cast your law behind their back and killed your prophets, who had
        warned them in order to turn them back to you, and they committed great blasphemies. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Therefore you gave them into the hand of their enemies, who made
        them suffer. And in the time of their suffering they cried out to you and
        you heard them from heaven, and according to your great mercies you gave
        them saviors who saved them from the hand of their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But after they had rest they did evil again before you, and you abandoned
        them to the hand of their enemies, so that they had dominion over them. Yet
        when they turned and cried to you, you heard from heaven, and many times
        you delivered them according to your mercies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And you warned them in order to turn them back to your law. Yet they
        acted presumptuously and did not obey your commandments, but sinned against
        your rules, which if a person does them, he shall live by them, and they
        turned a stubborn shoulder and stiffened their neck and would not obey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Many years you bore with them and warned them by your Spirit through
        your prophets. Yet they would not give ear. Therefore you gave them into
        the hand of the peoples of the lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Nevertheless, in your great mercies you did not make an end of them
        or forsake them, for you are a gracious and merciful God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CNow, therefore, our God, the great, the mighty, and the awesome
        God, who keeps covenant and steadfast love, let not all the hardship seem
        little to you that has come upon us, upon our kings, our princes, our priests,
        our prophets, our fathers, and all your people, since the time of the kings
        of Assyria until this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Yet you have been righteous in all that has come upon us, for you
        have dealt faithfully and we have acted wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Our kings, our princes, our priests, and our fathers have not kept
        your law or paid attention to your commandments and your warnings that you
        gave them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Even in their own kingdom, and amid your great goodness that you
        gave them, and in the large and rich land that you set before them, they
        did not serve you or turn from their wicked works. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Behold, we are slaves this day; in the land that you gave to our
        fathers to enjoy its fruit and its good gifts, behold, we are slaves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And its rich yield goes to the kings whom you have set over us because
        of our sins. They rule over our bodies and over our livestock as they please,
        and we are in great distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "  [[COMMENT(0)]] \u201CBecause of all this we make a firm covenant
        in writing; on the sealed document are the names of our princes, our Levites,
        and our priests."
      comments:
      - number: '9:38 '
        content: '  Ch 10:1 in Hebrew  Hebrew lacks '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The People Who Sealed the Covenant'
      title: The People Who Sealed the Covenant
      number: 1
      content: "    [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201COn the seals are the names of Nehemiah
        the governor, the son of Hacaliah, Zedekiah, "
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: '  Ch 10:2 in Hebrew  Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah; these are the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of
        Henadad, Kadmiel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and their brothers, Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Hodiah, Bani, Beninu. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The chiefs of the people: Parosh, Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Ahiah, Hanan, Anan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: The Obligations of the Covenant'
      title: The Obligations of the Covenant
      number: 27
      content: 'Malluch, Harim, Baanah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  \u201CThe rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers,
        the singers, the temple servants, and all who have separated themselves from
        the peoples of the lands to the Law of God, their wives, their sons, their
        daughters, all who have knowledge and understanding, "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "join with their brothers, their nobles, and enter into a curse and
        an oath to walk in God\u2019s Law that was given by Moses the servant of
        God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our Lord and his rules and his statutes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'We will not give our daughters to the peoples of the land or take
        their daughters for our sons. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And if the peoples of the land bring in goods or any grain on the
        Sabbath day to sell, we will not buy from them on the Sabbath or on a holy
        day. And we will forego the crops of the seventh year and the exaction of
        every debt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CWe also take on ourselves the obligation to give yearly a third
        part of a shekel[[COMMENT(0)]] for the service of the house of our God: "
      comments:
      - number: '10:32 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'for the showbread, the regular grain offering, the regular burnt
        offering, the Sabbaths, the new moons, the appointed feasts, the holy things,
        and the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and for all the work
        of the house of our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "We, the priests, the Levites, and the people, have likewise cast
        lots for the wood offering, to bring it into the house of our God, according
        to our fathers\u2019 houses, at times appointed, year by year, to burn on
        the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God, as it is written in
        the Law. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'We obligate ourselves to bring the firstfruits of our ground and
        the firstfruits of all fruit of every tree, year by year, to the house of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'also to bring to the house of our God, to the priests who minister
        in the house of our God, the firstborn of our sons and of our cattle, as
        it is written in the Law, and the firstborn of our herds and of our flocks; '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and to bring the first of our dough, and our contributions, the fruit
        of every tree, the wine and the oil, to the priests, to the chambers of the
        house of our God; and to bring to the Levites the tithes from our ground,
        for it is the Levites who collect the tithes in all our towns where we labor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And the priest, the son of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when
        the Levites receive the tithes. And the Levites shall bring up the tithe
        of the tithes to the house of our God, to the chambers of the storehouse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "For the people of Israel and the sons of Levi shall bring the contribution
        of grain, wine, and oil to the chambers, where the vessels of the sanctuary
        are, as well as the priests who minister, and the gatekeepers and the singers.
        We will not neglect the house of our God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Leaders in Jerusalem'
      title: The Leaders in Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the leaders of the people lived in Jerusalem. And the rest
        of the people cast lots to bring one out of ten to live in Jerusalem the
        holy city, while nine out of ten[[COMMENT(0)]] remained in the other towns. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the people blessed all the men who willingly offered to live
        in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "  These are the chiefs of the province who lived in Jerusalem; but
        in the towns of Judah everyone lived on his property in their towns: Israel,
        the priests, the Levites, the temple servants, and the descendants of Solomon\u2019s
        servants. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And in Jerusalem lived certain of the sons of Judah and of the sons
        of Benjamin. Of the sons of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, son of Zechariah,
        son of Amariah, son of Shephatiah, son of Mahalalel, of the sons of Perez; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and Maaseiah the son of Baruch, son of Col-hozeh, son of Hazaiah,
        son of Adaiah, son of Joiarib, son of Zechariah, son of the Shilonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All the sons of Perez who lived in Jerusalem were 468 valiant men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And these are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, son
        of Joed, son of Pedaiah, son of Kolaiah, son of Maaseiah, son of Ithiel,
        son of Jeshaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and his brothers, men of valor, 928.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer; and Judah the son of Hassenuah
        was second over the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of
        Meraioth, son of Ahitub, ruler of the house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'and their brothers who did the work of the house, 822; and Adaiah
        the son of Jeroham, son of Pelaliah, son of Amzi, son of Zechariah, son of
        Pashhur, son of Malchijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and his brothers, heads of fathers\u2019 houses, 242; and Amashsai,
        the son of Azarel, son of Ahzai, son of Meshillemoth, son of Immer, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and their brothers, mighty men of valor, 128; their overseer was
        Zabdiel the son of Haggedolim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam,
        son of Hashabiah, son of Bunni; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the chiefs of the Levites, who were
        over the outside work of the house of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'and Mattaniah the son of Mica, son of Zabdi, son of Asaph, who was
        the leader of the praise,[[COMMENT(0)]] who gave thanks, and Bakbukiah, the
        second among his brothers; and Abda the son of Shammua, son of Galal, son
        of Jeduthun. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:17 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All the Levites in the holy city were 284.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon and their brothers, who kept watch
        at the gates, were 172. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And the rest of Israel, and of the priests and the Levites, were
        in all the towns of Judah, every one in his inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But the temple servants lived on Ophel; and Ziha and Gishpa were
        over the temple servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani,
        son of Hashabiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Mica, of the sons of Asaph, the
        singers, over the work of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For there was a command from the king concerning them, and a fixed
        provision for the singers, as every day required. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Villages Outside Jerusalem'
      title: Villages Outside Jerusalem
      number: 24
      content: "And Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the sons of Zerah the son
        of Judah, was at the king\u2019s side[[COMMENT(0)]] in all matters concerning
        the people.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And as for the villages, with their fields, some of the people of
        Judah lived in Kiriath-arba and its villages, and in Dibon and its villages,
        and in Jekabzeel and its villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and in Jeshua and in Moladah and Beth-pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'in Hazar-shual, in Beersheba and its villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'in Ziklag, in Meconah and its villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'in En-rimmon, in Zorah, in Jarmuth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages, Lachish and its fields, and
        Azekah and its villages. So they encamped from Beersheba to the Valley of
        Hinnom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The people of Benjamin also lived from Geba onward, at Michmash,
        Aija, Bethel and its villages, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Lod, and Ono, the valley of craftsmen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: And certain divisions of the Levites in Judah were assigned to Benjamin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Priests and Levites'
      title: Priests and Levites
      number: 1
      content: '  These are the priests and the Levites who came up with Zerubbabel
        the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the chiefs of the priests
        and of their brothers in the days of Jeshua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah,
        who with his brothers was in charge of the songs of thanksgiving. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Bakbukiah and Unni and their brothers stood opposite them in
        the service. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Jeshua was the father of Joiakim, Joiakim the father of Eliashib,
        Eliashib the father of Joiada, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Joiada the father of Jonathan, and Jonathan the father of Jaddua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  And in the days of Joiakim were priests, heads of fathers\u2019
        houses: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah; "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'of Malluchi, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethanel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "In the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, and Jaddua, the Levites
        were recorded as heads of fathers\u2019 houses; so too were the priests in
        the reign of Darius the Persian. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "As for the sons of Levi, their heads of fathers\u2019 houses were
        written in the Book of the Chronicles until the days of Johanan the son of
        Eliashib. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the chiefs of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the
        son of Kadmiel, with their brothers who stood opposite them, to praise and
        to give thanks, according to the commandment of David the man of God, watch
        by watch. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were
        gatekeepers standing guard at the storehouses of the gates. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: Dedication of the Wall'
      title: Dedication of the Wall
      number: 26
      content: 'These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua son of Jozadak,
        and in the days of Nehemiah the governor and of Ezra, the priest and scribe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites
        in all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem to celebrate the dedication
        with gladness, with thanksgivings and with singing, with cymbals, harps,
        and lyres. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the sons of the singers gathered together from the district surrounding
        Jerusalem and from the villages of the Netophathites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'also from Beth-gilgal and from the region of Geba and Azmaveth, for
        the singers had built for themselves villages around Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the priests and the Levites purified themselves, and they purified
        the people and the gates and the wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then I brought the leaders of Judah up onto the wall and appointed
        two great choirs that gave thanks. One went to the south on the wall to the
        Dung Gate. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And after them went Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'and Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, and Jeremiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "and certain of the priests\u2019 sons with trumpets: Zechariah the
        son of Jonathan, son of Shemaiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Micaiah, son of
        Zaccur, son of Asaph; "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and his relatives, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel,
        Judah, and Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God.
        And Ezra the scribe went before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'At the Fountain Gate they went up straight before them by the stairs
        of the city of David, at the ascent of the wall, above the house of David,
        to the Water Gate on the east.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '  The other choir of those who gave thanks went to the north, and
        I followed them with half of the people, on the wall, above the Tower of
        the Ovens, to the Broad Wall, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and above the Gate of Ephraim, and by the Gate of Yeshanah,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and by the Fish Gate and the Tower of Hananel and the Tower of the Hundred,
        to the Sheep Gate; and they came to a halt at the Gate of the Guard. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:39 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So both choirs of those who gave thanks stood in the house of God,
        and I and half of the officials with me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'and the priests Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah,
        and Hananiah, with trumpets; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam,
        and Ezer. And the singers sang with Jezrahiah as their leader. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: Service at the Temple'
      title: Service at the Temple
      number: 43
      content: 'And they offered great sacrifices that day and rejoiced, for God
        had made them rejoice with great joy; the women and children also rejoiced.
        And the joy of Jerusalem was heard far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: '  On that day men were appointed over the storerooms, the contributions,
        the firstfruits, and the tithes, to gather into them the portions required
        by the Law for the priests and for the Levites according to the fields of
        the towns, for Judah rejoiced over the priests and the Levites who ministered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And they performed the service of their God and the service of purification,
        as did the singers and the gatekeepers, according to the command of David
        and his son Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'For long ago in the days of David and Asaph there were directors
        of the singers, and there were songs[[COMMENT(0)]] of praise and thanksgiving
        to God. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:46 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: And all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel and in the days of Nehemiah
        gave the daily portions for the singers and the gatekeepers; and they set
        apart that which was for the Levites; and the Levites set apart that which
        was for the sons of Aaron.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Nehemiah\u2019s Final Reforms"
      title: "Nehemiah\u2019s Final Reforms"
      number: 1
      content: '  On that day they read from the Book of Moses in the hearing of
        the people. And in it was found written that no Ammonite or Moabite should
        ever enter the assembly of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "for they did not meet the people of Israel with bread and water,
        but hired Balaam against them to curse them\u2014yet our God turned the curse
        into a blessing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As soon as the people heard the law, they separated from Israel all
        those of foreign descent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now before this, Eliashib the priest, who was appointed over the
        chambers of the house of our God, and who was related to Tobiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'prepared for Tobiah a large chamber where they had previously put
        the grain offering, the frankincense, the vessels, and the tithes of grain,
        wine, and oil, which were given by commandment to the Levites, singers, and
        gatekeepers, and the contributions for the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'While this was taking place, I was not in Jerusalem, for in the thirty-second
        year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon I went to the king. And after some time
        I asked leave of the king '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and came to Jerusalem, and I then discovered the evil that Eliashib
        had done for Tobiah, preparing for him a chamber in the courts of the house
        of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And I was very angry, and I threw all the household furniture of
        Tobiah out of the chamber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then I gave orders, and they cleansed the chambers, and I brought
        back there the vessels of the house of God, with the grain offering and the
        frankincense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I also found out that the portions of the Levites had not been given
        to them, so that the Levites and the singers, who did the work, had fled
        each to his field. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So I confronted the officials and said, \u201CWhy is the house of
        God forsaken?\u201D And I gathered them together and set them in their stations. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then all Judah brought the tithe of the grain, wine, and oil into
        the storehouses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And I appointed as treasurers over the storehouses Shelemiah the
        priest, Zadok the scribe, and Pedaiah of the Levites, and as their assistant
        Hanan the son of Zaccur, son of Mattaniah, for they were considered reliable,
        and their duty was to distribute to their brothers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and do not wipe out my good
        deeds that I have done for the house of my God and for his service.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In those days I saw in Judah people treading winepresses on the Sabbath,
        and bringing in heaps of grain and loading them on donkeys, and also wine,
        grapes, figs, and all kinds of loads, which they brought into Jerusalem on
        the Sabbath day. And I warned them on the day when they sold food. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Tyrians also, who lived in the city, brought in fish and all kinds
        of goods and sold them on the Sabbath to the people of Judah, in Jerusalem
        itself! '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then I confronted the nobles of Judah and said to them, \u201CWhat
        is this evil thing that you are doing, profaning the Sabbath day? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Did not your fathers act in this way, and did not our God bring all
        this disaster[[COMMENT(0)]] on us and on this city? Now you are bringing
        more wrath on Israel by profaning the Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:18 '
        content: The Hebrew word can mean , , or , depending on the context
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'As soon as it began to grow dark at the gates of Jerusalem before
        the Sabbath, I commanded that the doors should be shut and gave orders that
        they should not be opened until after the Sabbath. And I stationed some of
        my servants at the gates, that no load might be brought in on the Sabbath
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the merchants and sellers of all kinds of wares lodged outside
        Jerusalem once or twice. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But I warned them and said to them, \u201CWhy do you lodge outside
        the wall? If you do so again, I will lay hands on you.\u201D From that time
        on they did not come on the Sabbath. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then I commanded the Levites that they should purify themselves and
        come and guard the gates, to keep the Sabbath day holy. Remember this also
        in my favor, O my God, and spare me according to the greatness of your steadfast
        love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In those days also I saw the Jews who had married women of Ashdod,
        Ammon, and Moab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod, and they
        could not speak the language of Judah, but only the language of each people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And I confronted them and cursed them and beat some of them and pulled
        out their hair. And I made them take an oath in the name of God, saying,
        \u201CYou shall not give your daughters to their sons, or take their daughters
        for your sons or for yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Did not Solomon king of Israel sin on account of such women? Among
        the many nations there was no king like him, and he was beloved by his God,
        and God made him king over all Israel. Nevertheless, foreign women made even
        him to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Shall we then listen to you and do all this great evil and act treacherously
        against our God by marrying foreign women?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And one of the sons of Jehoiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest,
        was the son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonite. Therefore I chased him from
        me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Remember them, O my God, because they have desecrated the priesthood
        and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Thus I cleansed them from everything foreign, and I established
        the duties of the priests and Levites, each in his work; '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: and I provided for the wood offering at appointed times, and for the
        firstfruits.  Remember me, O my God, for good.
      comments: []
